{{Orphan|date=October 2006}} 
'''iRam''' is a new application of an old technology from [[Gigabyte Technology]]. It basically involves a [[PCI card]] with slots for up to 4[[Gigabyte|GB]] of [[DDR DRAM]] which is used like a normal disk drive. Their recommended application of this drive is to install an [[operating system]] on it, in order to increase [[booting]] speed. They claim an increase in up to 60-times the speed and can boot [[Windows XP]] in 5 seconds. 

