A '''Member of Technical Staff''' ('''MTS''') is the title for permanent research staff at some institutions and companies. It is roughly equivalent to an [[assistant professor]] or [[associate professor]] at a [[university]] or a [[chief technical officer]] (CTO) in a technology [[startup company]].<ref name="colloquial">[http://www.colloquial.com/carp/mts.html Members of Technical Staff], [http://www.colloquial.com/ Colloguial.com].</ref>
A '''Distinguished Member of Technical Staff''' ('''DMTS''') is roughly equivalent to a [[full professor]] (or [[emeritus professor]]) at a university or a [[chief executive officer]] (CEO) of a technology startup company. The term is especially used at [[Bell Labs]].<ref name="colloquial" /> Other related title used include:<ref>[http://www.glassdoor.com/Salaries/Member-of-Technical-Staff-Salary-SRCH_KO0,25.htm Member of Technical Staff Salaries], [http://www.glassdoor.com/ glassdoor.com].</ref>
