[[ja:コストパフォーマンス]]

'''Bridge Communications, Inc.''' was founded by [[Judy Estrin]] and [[William N. Carrico, Jr.|Bill Carrico]] in 1981 and was based in Mountain View, California. Bridge Communications made computer network [[Bridging (networking)|bridges]], [[routers]], and [[communications server]]s.<ref>{{cite web|title= Meet the Bellbusters |date=2001-11-01|name=Steve Silberman|url=http://www.wired.com/wired/archive/9.11/billnjudy.html?pg=1}}</ref> They specialized in inter-connecting different kinds of networks.

Bridge Communications shipped the first commercial router.<ref>{{cite web|title=NerdTV #13: Judy Estrin|publisher=[[PBS]]|date=2006-04-10|url=http://www.pbs.org/cringely/nerdtv/transcripts/013.html}}</ref>

Bridge Communications was acquired by 3COM on September 30, 1987.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bridge Communications, Inc.|publisher=[[Business Week]]|url=http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=25769}}</ref>

